AttributeList.Text: Written BY Kristopher Gimenez Feb 3,2023 This block is used to control the TD Oscillator
Variables set to zero, will be set based on current control state

On startup set current position as Zero. Adjust Home position by Bump value Calculate new endpoints for oscillator. Osc Home High and Low are used for warnings while Holding positiong. Note High position is 2x Rotational Deg per count above home while low is just 1 deg per count below home Note: Bump Inputs are set on HMI . If holding they will be reset when bump finished moving, if not holding reset the bits.
Set State to zero if first block call State Zero - Startup and set to reset bits and go to Waiting Cmd
Stop command from any state. If Stop received while holding position, stop and wait for new command. If stop received while Oscillating, go to stop Oscillating.
Nothing happens in State 1 Awaiting Command- Placeholder Network if actions needed here.
Set Home Position as current position. Enable Selected pump in Rev and send Min Command.

If no Bump Received - Position Held - Maintain output - Position Above home(increasing) - Stroke Hold - - Position Below Home (decreasing) - Stroke Min - Flow Rev Enabled If bump received go to Bump/Reactive Bump and set new Home

Move quill to new position in the FWD direction. Start at Min and Ramp up until speed reach. If Approaching Torq Limit, limit output flow. At or above new home position, output min and hold position Note: Dummy Move On Maintain speed there as visual only.

Allow the quill to reactively move to the new position. Flow Rev enabled to Min until at Home position. If position below start position, min too high and moving wrong direction. Not reacting. At or above new home position, hold position

Move quill to new position in the Rev direction. Start at Hold mA and Ramp up until speed reach. If Approaching Torq Limit, limit output flow. At or above new home position, output hold value and hold position Note: Dummy Move On Maintain speed there as visual only.
Toggel Pump Use when starting. Store starting values and calculate target positions

Move quill to FWD end position in the FWD direction. Start at Min and Ramp up until speed reach. If Approaching Torq Limit, limit output flow. At or above end position, switch direction Note: Dummy Move On Maintain speed there as visual only.

Move quill to new position in the Rev direction. Start at Hold mA and Ramp up until speed reach. If Approaching Torq Limit, limit output flow. At or above new home position, output hold value and hold position Note: Dummy Move On Maintain speed there as visual only.
Determine current position and direction to Home position

Move quill FWD to the home position Start at Min and Ramp up until speed reach. If Approaching Torq Limit, limit output flow. At or above end position, switch direction Note: Dummy Move On Maintain speed there as visual only.

Move quill to Home position in the Rev direction. Start at Hold mA and Ramp up until speed reach. If Approaching Torq Limit, limit output flow. At or above new home position, output hold value and hold position Note: Dummy Move On Maintain speed there as visual only.
Torq is set based on Fwd torq setpoint and is enabled if not Stopped.
Torq always enabled in MU mode. Pumps alternate
